The paper deals with algorithms for approximating the optimal transport distance between two probability distributions, which involves optimization and linear programming. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CG (computational geometry), cs.IT (information theory), cs.LG (machine learning), or cs.NA (numerical analysis).
